  "text": "The upwind evaluation was preferred by Tu and Yuan, [CITATION_1] as it was expected to be more dissipative and thus more stable. We have considered both evaluations; a comparison will be shown in Section IV. We note that ∆Ŵ ± i+1/2 and ∆W ± i+1/2 are, respectively, high and low order upwind evaluations of the spatial increment of fluxes of the characteristic variables. They are limited according to:",
